Well, what I was saying is that the spec says &quot;to delete the resource 
*or move it to an inaccessible location* &quot;, so the resource is not 
necessarily deleted. Now I think a URI doesn&#39;t exist &quot;per se&quot; (or 
existing &quot;per se&quot; it points to nowhere, identifies nothing, for me is 
the same as &quot;don&#39;t exist&quot; in the sense it doesn&#39;t have a representation) 
so when I said &quot;delete the URI&quot; I should have said &quot;disassociate the URI 
from the resource&quot; to be accurate.

